.\" mysql.1 — man page for the Plakar MySQL integration plugin
.\" Process with: man ./mysql.1
.TH MYSQL 1 "April 2025" "Plakar MySQL Integration" "Plakar Plugins"
.SH NAME
mysql \- Plakar plugin for logical backup and restore of MySQL databases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B plakar backup
.I mysql://[user[:password]@]host[:port][/database]
.RI [ option = value " ...]"
.PP
.B plakar restore
.B \-to
.I mysql://[user[:password]@]host[:port][/database]
.RI [ option = value " ...]"
.I snapshot-id
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B mysql
Plakar plugin provides logical backup and restore of MySQL databases using
.BR mysqldump (1)
and
.BR mysql (1).
.PP
Backups produce standard SQL files that are human-readable and restorable
without Plakar.  Plakar adds deduplication, compression, encryption,
versioning, and remote storage on top.
.PP
When a database is specified in the URI, only that database is backed up
(single-database mode).  When no database is specified, all non-system
databases are backed up with
.BR --all-databases .
.SH CONNECTION URI
.PP
.nf
mysql://[user[:password]@]host[:port][/database]
.fi
.PP
.TS
tab(|);
l l.
Component|Default|Description
user| |MySQL username
password| |MySQL password (never on command line; uses MYSQL_PWD)
host|127.0.0.1|MySQL server hostname or IP address
port|3306|MySQL server port
database| |Database to back up (omit for all-databases mode)
.TE
.SH IMPORTER OPTIONS
Options are appended after the URI as
.IR key = value
pairs.
.TP
.B location
Full connection URI
.RB ( mysql:// \&...).
.TP
.B host
Server hostname. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B port
Server port (default:
.BR 3306 ).
Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B username
MySQL username. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B password
MySQL password. Overrides the URI.
Passed to commands via the
.B MYSQL_PWD
environment variable, never via the command line.
.TP
.B database
Name of the database to back up. Overrides the URI database path.
When omitted,
.BR mysqldump " --all-databases"
is used.
.TP
.B single_transaction
Boolean (default:
.BR true ).
Use
.B --single-transaction
for a consistent InnoDB snapshot without table locks.
Strongly recommended for production InnoDB databases.
Has no effect on MyISAM tables.
.TP
.B routines
Boolean (default:
.BR true ).
Include stored procedures and functions
.RB ( --routines ).
.TP
.B events
Boolean (default:
.BR true ).
Include event scheduler events
.RB ( --events ).
.TP
.B triggers
Boolean (default:
.BR true ).
Include triggers.
Set to
.B false
to pass
.B --skip-triggers
to mysqldump.
.TP
.B schema_only
Boolean (default:
.BR false ).
Dump DDL only, no data
.RB ( --no-data ).
Mutually exclusive with
.BR data_only .
.TP
.B data_only
Boolean (default:
.BR false ).
Dump data only, no DDL
.RB ( --no-create-info ).
Mutually exclusive with
.BR schema_only .
.TP
.B hex_blob
Boolean (default:
.BR false ).
Encode BINARY, VARBINARY, BLOB, and BIT columns using hexadecimal notation
.RB ( --hex-blob ).
Useful for cross-platform portability.
.TP
.B set_gtid_purged
String:
.BR AUTO ,
.BR ON ,
or
.B OFF
(default:
.BR AUTO ).
Controls the
.B SET @@GLOBAL.GTID_PURGED
statement in the dump.
.B AUTO
includes it only when GTIDs are enabled on the server.
Use
.B OFF
when restoring to a server with existing GTID history.
.TP
.B mysql_bin_dir
Directory containing the
.B mysqldump
and
.B mysql
binaries.
When omitted, binaries are resolved via
.BR $PATH .
.TP
.B ssl_mode
SSL/TLS mode:
.BR disabled ,
.BR preferred ,
.BR required ,
.BR verify_ca ,
or
.BR verify_identity .
Passed as
.B --ssl-mode
to mysqldump and mysql.
.TP
.B ssl_cert
Path to the client SSL certificate file (PEM format).
.TP
.B ssl_key
Path to the client SSL private key file (PEM format).
.TP
.B ssl_ca
Path to the CA certificate file used to verify the server (PEM format).
.SH EXPORTER OPTIONS
.TP
.B location
Full connection URI
.RB ( mysql:// \&...).
.TP
.B host
Server hostname. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B port
Server port. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B username
MySQL username. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B password
MySQL password. Overrides the URI.
.TP
.B database
Target database for restore.
When omitted, the database name is inferred from the dump filename
(e.g.
.I mydb.sql
→
.IR mydb ).
Not used when restoring an
.I all.sql
dump.
.TP
.B create_db
Boolean (default:
.BR false ).
Issue
.B CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS
before restoring a single-database dump.
.TP
.B force
Boolean (default:
.BR false ).
Pass
.B --force
to
.BR mysql (1)
so restore continues after SQL errors.
.TP
.B mysql_bin_dir
Directory containing the
.B mysql
binary.
.TP
.B ssl_mode , ssl_cert , ssl_key , ssl_ca
Same as the importer options.
.SH SNAPSHOT LAYOUT
.TS
tab(|);
l l.
Path|Contents
/manifest.json|Server metadata (version, config, databases, tables, routines, triggers, events)
/<database>.sql|Single-database dump (when database is specified)
/all.sql|Full-server dump (when database is omitted)
.TE
.SH EXAMPLES
Back up a single database:
.PP
.nf
plakar backup mysql://dbuser:secret@db.example.com/mydb
.fi
.PP
Back up all databases:
.PP
.nf
plakar backup mysql://root:secret@db.example.com
.fi
.PP
Back up schema only:
.PP
.nf
plakar backup "mysql://dbuser:secret@db.example.com/mydb schema_only=true"
.fi
.PP
Restore to an existing database:
.PP
.nf
plakar restore -to mysql://dbuser:secret@target.example.com/mydb abc1234
.fi
.PP
Restore and create the database first:
.PP
.nf
plakar restore -to "mysql://root:secret@target.example.com/mydb create_db=true" abc1234
.fi
.PP
Restore all databases:
.PP
.nf
plakar restore -to mysql://root:secret@target.example.com abc1234
.fi
.PP
Use non-standard binary location and TLS:
.PP
.nf
plakar backup "mysql://dbuser:secret@db.example.com/mydb \\
  mysql_bin_dir=/usr/local/mysql/bin \\
  ssl_mode=verify_identity \\
  ssl_ca=/etc/mysql/ca.pem"
.fi
.SH REQUIRED PRIVILEGES
For single-database backup with
.B single_transaction
(recommended):
.PP
.nf
GRANT SELECT, SHOW VIEW, TRIGGER, EVENT ON mydb.* TO 'backup'@'%';
GRANT PROCESS ON *.* TO 'backup'@'%';
.fi
.PP
For all-databases backup:
.PP
.nf
GRANT SELECT, SHOW VIEW, TRIGGER, LOCK TABLES, EVENT, RELOAD ON *.* TO 'backup'@'%';
GRANT PROCESS ON *.* TO 'backup'@'%';
.fi
.SH NOTES
.SS InnoDB and single_transaction
The
.B single_transaction
option (enabled by default) takes a consistent read snapshot for the entire
dump without acquiring table locks.  This is strongly recommended for
production InnoDB databases.
.PP
MyISAM tables require table locks regardless of
.BR single_transaction .
Consider migrating MyISAM tables to InnoDB for lock-free backups.
.SS GTIDs
When GTIDs are enabled on the source server, the dump includes
.B SET @@GLOBAL.GTID_PURGED
statements.  Restoring such a dump to a server with existing GTID history
will fail.  Set
.B set_gtid_purged=OFF
to omit these statements, or run
.B RESET MASTER
on the target before restoring.
.SS Users and grants
Single-database dumps do not include MySQL user accounts or grants.  Use an
all-databases backup (which includes the
.I mysql
system database) or migrate grants manually using
.BR pt-show-grants (1)
from the Percona Toolkit.
.SH LIMITATIONS
Physical backups are not supported in v1.
Only logical dumps via
.BR mysqldump (1)
are implemented.
Per-table filtering, restore-time schema/data filtering, and user/grant
migration for single-database backups are planned for future versions.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR plakar (1),
.BR mysqldump (1),
.BR mysql (1)
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/PlakarKorp/integration-mysql/issues
